# UI Component Usage Rules

This project uses **Vue 3 + TypeScript + Tailwind** with a centralized component system.

All UI primitives must come from the `/components` directory.

The goal is to maintain a **consistent design system and prevent style drift**.

---

## Core Rule

Never create UI primitives directly inside pages or feature modules.

Always import them from `/components`.

UI primitives include:

- Button
- Input
- Textarea
- Select
- Checkbox
- Radio
- Modal
- Dialog
- Card
- Badge
- Tabs
- Dropdown
- Form fields
- Toggle
- Avatar
- Tooltip

Example:

import Button from "@/components/Button.vue"
import Input from "@/components/Input.vue"

Never write inline primitives such as:

<button class="bg-blue-500 px-4 py-2">Submit</button>
<input class="border p-2"/>

---

## Styling Rules

Component styling must **not be overridden inline**.

Forbidden:

<Button class="bg-red-500 text-xs rounded-none">

Allowed:

<Button>Save</Button>

Layout utilities are allowed **only on containers**.

Example:

<div class="flex justify-end mt-4">
  <Button>Save</Button>
</div>

---

## Creating New Components

If a UI element does not exist:

1. Do NOT implement it inline in a page
2. Create a reusable component inside `/components`
3. Implement styling using theme tokens
4. Import it where needed

Example workflow:

Step 1 — create component

/components/UserAvatar.vue

Step 2 — implement reusable logic

Step 3 — import in page

import UserAvatar from "@/components/UserAvatar.vue"

---

## Page Layer Restrictions

Pages should only:

- compose existing components
- handle layout
- fetch data
- connect stores

Pages must NOT:

- define reusable UI primitives
- duplicate component logic
- contain large UI blocks that belong in components

---

## Reusability Rule

If UI logic or template exceeds **15–20 lines**, extract it into `/components`.

Bad:

/views/dashboard.vue
300 lines of UI

Good:

/components/DashboardCard.vue
/views/dashboard.vue

---

## AI Code Generation Rule

When generating UI code:

1. Check `/components` first
2. Reuse existing components
3. If missing → create a new component in `/components`
4. Never generate raw HTML primitives inside pages
